post_text: Parents/Guardians, please be patient...the information is being mailed with everything you will need to know for hybrid and virtual learning. The virtual students had a schedule to pick up their chromebooks at Bogalusa High School this past week. The hybrid students will be given their chromebooks at the school after the appropriate paperwork is filled out and returned to school. Thank you so much!
shared_text:
Byrd Avenue Primary
September 3 at 11:01 PM ¬∑

Parents/Guardians please be checking for important mail soon. We have mailed out letters letting you know if your child is attending on Hybrid Days- A or B, or if they are an all Virtual student.

Hybrid information- If your child is an A student, he or she will come on Monday and Tuesday‚Äôs with distant learning on Wednesday, Thursday, & Friday.

If your child is a B student, he or she will come on Thursday and Friday with distant learning on Monday, Tuesday, & Wednesday.

All Virtual students will participate Monday - Friday in a combination of virtual lessons with direct teaching and distant learning/independent lessons. Suggested family and student schedules will be sent home in their bags during our Virtual Mini open house on Friday, September 4th. Also important information will be posted on our Byrd Avenue Website, and Byrd Avenue Primary‚Äôs facebook page. Thanks for your continued patience as we navigate this unusual start of a successful school year! üòÉ

We've partnered with NOGGIN, Nickelodeon's learning service for children age 2 and above. Noggin is extending its free offer for an additional 90 days. The app is loaded with read-aloud e-books, learning games, songs, and other engaging content. It also provides ideas for off-screen family activities, and it provides special content to help young children cope during this time.

Sign up here: https://www.noggin.com/noggin-cares-louisiana/

May 4 at 3:28 PM ¬∑

IMPORTANT ANNOUNCEMENT

Beginning this week, Grab and Go lunch and breakfasts will be Mondays and Thursdays, instead of Mondays and Wednesdays. We are happy to announce this change is because students will now be receiving meals for 7 days instead of 5. Pick-up locations will continue to be at BHS and Byrd Avenue schools. At BHS, the pick-up spot will be behind the gym and cafeteria. There will be tables set up for pick up. At Byrd Avenue, the pick-up will be in front of the school.

There will be a change in our student meal delivery in the coming week. Beginning Monday March 23 we will deliver 3 days a week instead of 5. We will deliver Monday, Wednesday, and Friday. Same time same stops. Two breakfasts and lunches per child we be delivered on Monday and Wednesday and one on Friday.

Thank you so much for your patience and continued gratitude during this time. Stay safe and healthy!

Superintendent Lisa Tanner
